================================================================================
Installing ONIE on:
Mellanox MSX1400/MSX1700 Series w/ Intel(R) Core(TM) i7-3612QE Module
Mellanox MSX6710 Series w/ Intel(R) Celeron(R) CPU 1047UE Module
================================================================================

Cross-Compiling ONIE
====================

Change directories to "build-config" to compile ONIE.

To compile ONIE first change directories to "build-config" and then
type "make BUILDDIR=<your builddir> MACHINE=mlnx_x86 MACHINEROOT=../machine/mellanox all <other targets>".
For example:

  $ cd build-config
  $ make -j4 BUILDDIR=<your builddir> MACHINEROOT=../machine/mellanox MACHINE=mlnx_x86 all recovery-initrd demo mellanox-net-boot-label

When complete, the ONIE binaries are located in
"<BUILDDIR>/images":

demo-diag-installer-x86_64-mlnx_x86-r0.bin
demo-installer-x86_64-mlnx_x86-r0.bin
mellanox_net_boot_label.sh
mlnx_x86-r0.initrd
mlnx_x86-r0.vmlinuz
onie-updater-x86_64-mlnx_x86-r0
recovery-x86_64-mlnx_x86-r0.initrd

